# UniFi Express Provider

The UniFi Express provider enables infrastructure-as-code management of [Ubiquiti's UniFi Express](https://www.ui.com/) devices running **Network Application 8.x**. This is a fork of [filipowm/terraform-provider-unifi](https://github.com/filipowm/terraform-provider-unifi) targeting the UniFi Express hardware specifically.

## Supported Features

- Manage UniFi Express network resources using Infrastructure as Code
- Targets **Network Application 8.x** (the version running on UniFi Express)
- Username/password authentication only
- 30+ resources including:
    - Network/WLAN configuration
    - Firewall rules, groups, zones, and policies
    - Port forwarding and port profiles
    - DNS records
    - User management
    - Device management
    - Settings (guest access, DPI, NTP, management, and more)

## Supported Platform

- **UniFi Express** running Network Application 8.x

The provider enforces version constraints and will reject connections to controllers outside the 8.x range.

## Removed Resources

The following resources are **not supported** on UniFi Express and have been removed:

- `unifi_setting_ips` — No IDS/IPS on Express hardware
- `unifi_setting_ssl_inspection` — Requires IPS
- `unifi_setting_lcd_monitor` — No LCD panel on Express

## Authentication

The provider supports **username/password authentication only**. API Key authentication requires controller version 9.0.108+, which is not available on the Express.

!> Hard-coding credentials into any Terraform configuration is not recommended, and risks secret leakage should this file ever be committed to a public version control system.

### Security Recommendations

- Create a dedicated local admin account for Terraform
- Use a **Limited Admin** role with **Local Access Only**
- Store credentials securely using Terraform variables or environment variables
- Two-factor authentication (2FA) is not supported

